section.section:
The secretary shall appoint the Perinatal Advisory Committee to make recommendations for the improvement of the following statewide health status indicators that relate to pregnancy and perinatal care:
Infant mortality;
Preterm birth;
Substance abuse during pregnancy;
Neonatal withdrawal syndrome, also called neonatal abstinence syndrome (NAS); and
Maternal mortality.

text.section:
The advisory committee shall be attached to the cabinet for administrative purposes and be composed of the following members:
The director of the Division of Maternal and Child Health, Department for Public Health, who shall serve as chair of the advisory committee;
The director of the Division of Maternal-Fetal Medicine, University of Kentucky College of Medicine;
The director of the Division of Maternal-Fetal Medicine, University of Louisville School of Medicine;
The director of a maternal-fetal medicine program from a pediatric teaching hospital with a Level III NICU that has a minimum of thirty (30) beds, to be selected by the secretary;
The director of the Division of Neonatology, University of Kentucky College of Medicine;
The director of the Division of Neonatology, University of Louisville School of Medicine;
One (1) practicing obstetrician from rural practice in a hospital with a Level I nursery, to be selected by the secretary;
One (1) practicing obstetrician from rural practice in a hospital with a Level II neonatal intensive care unit (NICU), to be selected by the secretary;
One (1) practicing pediatrician from rural practice in a hospital with a Level I nursery, to be selected by the secretary;
One (1) practicing pediatrician or one (1) practicing neonatologist from rural practice in a hospital with a Level II NICU, to be selected by the secretary;
One (1) practicing pediatrician or one (1) practicing neonatologist from a non-university urban practice hospital with a Level II NICU, to be selected by the secretary;
One (1) practicing pediatrician or one (1) practicing neonatologist from a pediatric teaching hospital with a Level III NICU that has a minimum of thirty (30) beds, to be selected by the secretary;
The president of the Kentucky Perinatal Association or designee;
The president of the Kentucky Academy of Family Practice or designee;
The president of the Kentucky Chapter of the American Academy of Pediatrics or designee;
The president of the Kentucky Section of the American College of Obstetricians and Gynecologists or designee;
